1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual perception and recognition of objects in real images. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also highly likely as the paper discusses the challenge of enabling communication between humans and robots, which is a core problem in robotics. 
3. cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is another likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a Navigator-Pointer model which is an AI-based approach to solving the problem. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the proposed model is based on machine learning techniques.
